solution:
The largest common factor of $9x^2$ and $3x$ is $3x$. We factor $3x$ out of each term to get\begin{align*}
9x^2+3x &= 3x\cdot 3x + 3x \cdot 1\\
&= \boxed{3x(3x+1)}.
\end{align*}

\[
\begin{array}{c|cc cc}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{x} & -5 \\
\cline{2-5}
x^2 + 5x + 1 & x^3& & &  \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{x^3} & +5x^2 & +x  \\
\cline{2-4}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & -5x^2 & -x & \\
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & -5x^2 & -25x & -5 \\
\cline{3-5}
\multicolumn{2}{r}{} & & 24x & +5 \\
\end{array}
\]Thus, the remainder is $\boxed{24x + 5}.$

